      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To audit your production VPC and IAM roles, you can use AWS services like AWS Config, AWS IAM Access Analyzer, or AWS CloudTrail to ensure that your IAM roles are adhering to the principle of least privilege. Here's a list of steps you can follow:\n\n1. Use AWS Config to assess, audit, and evaluate the configurations of your AWS resources.\n2. Use AWS IAM Access Analyzer to identify unused or overly permissive IAM roles.\n3. Review CloudTrail logs for any actions taken with the roles.\n4. Regularly review IAM policies attached to the roles and ensure they grant only the necessary permissions.\n5. Consider using tools like IAM Policy Simulator to test IAM permissions.\n\nOnce you identify roles with unnecessary permissions, you can adjust their policies accordingly. Always test changes in a non-production environment before applying them to your production environment to avoid unexpected disruptions.",
